Dabiegel 52nd Human Agnostic Monk of Crimson Defenders <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/ulittlecherub.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Little Cherub</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Love Doctor is In</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/12/02 6:09:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12439.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~mkdavid1/images/moglimini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interested in raid tactics, big to small</span><hr size=1> Well, I don't have any links but I can give you some advice sir.  This post is pretty much common sense, but hopefully you can learn a thing or two.  <br>
<br>
You've got the general idea that cutting down on spam is good, as is clear communication.  When you go on a raid just listen to the raid leader, hopefully he knows what he is doing.  Listen to his instructions and perform them to a T.  If you have a question, ask him or someone knowledgable!  Asking questions is NOT noob, it's how you learn, and it prevents you from killing everyone and really turning up like a dipshit.<br>
<br>
Don't wander around, just stick with the raid and resist the urge to peak around the corner, even though you have FD it can get you guys in trouble.  Don't get aggro either. =)<br>
<br>
Even in a pinch, try to keep your cool, if shit happens it's going to be your job to aid the corpse recovery.  Try to stick the fight out, but if you see that the end is near feign and wait for the dust to settle.  After a raid wipeout there are a couple different ways corpse recovery is going to happen:<br>
<br>
1) Everyone died in a safe spot.<br>
 a) If a cleric has camped out or you have someone there feigned with the ability to res, simply /q out, come back then ask in /gu or the raid channel something like &quot;=== Consent me now for a res, asshats===&quot;.  Then start dragging corpses to a convenient pile for the clerics to start clickin'.<br>
 b) If all the clerics are dead, the necros are dead, and no one has a Staff of Forbidden Rites (Vox res stick), notify people they need to get to the zone and prepare for a summon corpse<br>
<br>
2) Everyone died on top of mobs that aren't going to leave.<br>
 a) If the mobs aren't at their actual spawn spot and they're just being sticky, cordinate yourself with a cleric who is on another character (or a necro, person with res stick), plan to train the mob(s) far away so that he may log in and begin ressing.  Check your aggro for sure before coming back into camp so you don't train everyone.<br>
 b) If you guys died on top of a mobs spawn point you'll have to relocate camp for CR.  Hopefully you have a necro or res stick, if you have a cleric the only way for this to work is if you can train the mobs away and he can move to a safe spot without getting aggro, but this isn't likely.  So get consent, then begin dragging corpses to the safe spot where the necro or whoever is going to res a cleric so he can start clicking.<br>
<br>
3) Simplest scenario, you feigned, some clerics camped (or have necro, res stick) and the mobs eventually path away.  /q out then come back and get consent to drag the corpses to a pile.  Oh one last thing, inform people over /gu or the raidchannel before ressing that once they're ressed not to wander around.  It sounds like common sense, as does the rest of this post, but people sometimes do and gain aggro from nearby baddies.<br>
<br>
4) There are tons of other different variations on the previous situations, but just use that noggin' of yours and adapt, you'll do fine.<br>
<br>
If you plan on going on a raid where there is a good chance you may end up pulling, try to do some research in advance.  You can find maps at eqmaps.com or eqatlas.com.  Ask around or go to the zone ahead of time and see how the mobs path, how they aggro, the best route to get to the named mobs with less hassle.  You'll impress everyone with your well refined pulling technique as well.  Even if you don't get any compliments it's okay, too, people usually take good pulling for granted.<br>
<br>
Be courteous, kind, attentative and just use your head before acting and you'll do great on your raid!  You'll also impress others and surely gain a great reputation that shall allow you to get invited on more prestigious raids in the future.<br>
<br>
And most of all, HAVE FUN, it's not all about loot. <p><TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
